{
  "text": "Temporal analysis of the efficacy revealed that sufficient efficacy was not achieved in the patients whose infusion was terminated within 24 h, but became stable thereafter in those who underwent infusion therapy for up to 168 h or more. Previous studies of carperitide have demonstrated that significant hemodynamic improvements, including lowering of the pulmonary capillary wedge pressure and right atrial pressure, were maintained for 7 days of infusion of carperitide, associated with an increase in the cardiac index. [CITATION_1] ",
